⚙️ How It Works


1. Upload PDF        → PDF.js extracts text with positions
2. Click a word      → Speech engine starts from that word
3. Browser speaks    → Web Speech API reads text aloud
4. Words highlight   → onBoundary events track each word
5. Pauses inserted   → Punctuation-aware pause system
6. Auto-scroll       → Page follows the current word
No server. No cloud. Everything happens in your browser.

Text-to-Speech Pipeline


PDF → Extract Words with Positions → Build Speech Chunks
  → Analyze Pauses (punctuation, headings, paragraphs)
    → Detect Emphasis (bold, caps, key words)
      → Speak Sub-Chunks with Pauses Between
        → Track Words via onBoundary Events
          → Highlight Current Word in Real-Time

⌨️ Keyboard Shortcuts
Shortcut	Action
Space	Pause / Resume reading
Escape	Stop reading and clear highlights
?	Show keyboard shortcuts panel
Ctrl + =	Zoom in
Ctrl + -	Zoom out
Ctrl + 0	Fit to width
Ctrl + Scroll	Zoom with mouse wheel
Mouse Controls
